1
00:00:34,112 --> 00:00:35,380
(This drama is a work of fiction.)

2
00:00:35,380 --> 00:00:36,615
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

3
00:00:36,615 --> 00:00:37,849
(This drama complied
with production guidelines...)

4
00:00:37,849 --> 00:00:39,084
(for filming child actors and animals.)

5
00:00:48,627 --> 00:00:50,228
He killed someone?

6
00:00:58,003 --> 00:01:00,672
He was just drunk
and talking nonsense, right?

7
00:01:57,395 --> 00:02:04,369
(Episode 5
Setting the Limit)

8
00:02:55,921 --> 00:02:56,855
So he was...

9
00:02:57,822 --> 00:02:58,657
a soldier.

10
00:03:07,465 --> 00:03:11,703
(Gun Accident at Special Forces Guard Post
One Dead, One Critically Injured)

11
00:03:11,703 --> 00:03:13,505
"Special forces gun accident."

12
00:03:15,573 --> 00:03:16,708
(Senior Officer Dead)

13
00:03:16,708 --> 00:03:18,410
(Special Forces Gun Accident
Sergeant Yun Receives Three-year Sentence)

14
00:03:19,811 --> 00:03:20,679
"Three-year sentence."

15
00:03:21,313 --> 00:03:22,314
"Critically injured?"

16
00:03:25,850 --> 00:03:26,751
"Sergeant Yun."

17
00:03:27,886 --> 00:03:28,787
Could it be...

18
00:03:29,988 --> 00:03:30,922
Yun Deok Hyun?

19
00:03:36,695 --> 00:03:37,562
Weren't you...

20
00:03:38,530 --> 00:03:39,931
going to feed the cats?

21
00:03:40,732 --> 00:03:41,600
I was.

22
00:03:41,600 --> 00:03:42,968
But I left my phone behind.

23
00:03:46,104 --> 00:03:47,539
I lost my phone too,

24
00:03:48,373 --> 00:03:49,407
so I was looking for it.

25
00:03:50,575 --> 00:03:52,410
Sorry if I was intruding.

26
00:03:52,410 --> 00:03:53,278
Did you see it?

27
00:04:04,189 --> 00:04:05,023
Are you...

28
00:04:05,890 --> 00:04:07,525
the Sergeant Yun...

29
00:04:09,861 --> 00:04:11,062
who killed someone?

30
00:04:16,134 --> 00:04:17,002
You're not, right?

31
00:04:19,104 --> 00:04:19,938
If you're not,

32
00:04:20,472 --> 00:04:21,873
then just say so.

33
00:04:21,873 --> 00:04:24,376
Don't make me misunderstand.

34
00:04:25,110 --> 00:04:25,944
It's not...

35
00:04:28,380 --> 00:04:29,214
a misunderstanding.

36
00:04:33,652 --> 00:04:35,353
I was in prison for three years...

37
00:04:37,489 --> 00:04:38,490
for killing someone.

38
00:04:43,094 --> 00:04:43,962
Why...

39
00:04:46,197 --> 00:04:47,365
did you kill them?

40
00:04:49,434 --> 00:04:50,969
Because he deserved to die.

41
00:05:11,289 --> 00:05:12,257
Hey.

42
00:05:12,924 --> 00:05:13,792
Hey!

43
00:05:14,826 --> 00:05:15,994
What are you doing?

44
00:05:16,561 --> 00:05:17,963
You seemed to be feeling uncomfortable.

45
00:05:19,130 --> 00:05:19,965
I...

46
00:05:21,733 --> 00:05:23,068
It's not that...

47
00:05:25,837 --> 00:05:27,939
I can tell by the look on your face.

48
00:05:34,312 --> 00:05:35,580
Just throw away my diving suit.

49
00:05:37,115 --> 00:05:38,683
Deok Hyun, where are you going?

50
00:05:39,751 --> 00:05:41,586
Wait. Are you leaving for good?

51
00:05:41,853 --> 00:05:42,988
That's so sudden!

52
00:05:42,988 --> 00:05:44,589
What's going on?

53
00:05:44,589 --> 00:05:47,359
Deok Hyun. Are you really leaving?

54
00:05:47,525 --> 00:05:48,793
Deok Hyun!

55
00:05:54,966 --> 00:05:56,034
And who...

56
00:05:57,269 --> 00:05:58,136
is this guy?

57
00:05:58,436 --> 00:05:59,304
Well,

58
00:06:00,705 --> 00:06:01,740
I'm here to see her.

59
00:06:02,641 --> 00:06:03,441
You...

60
00:06:04,442 --> 00:06:05,777
were seeing someone?

61
00:06:08,680 --> 00:06:09,581
Cha Jae Yun.

62
00:06:10,649 --> 00:06:11,516
How did you...

63
00:06:11,883 --> 00:06:12,717
Isn't this a surprise?

64
00:06:13,618 --> 00:06:14,586
I'm shocked too.

65
00:06:16,087 --> 00:06:18,790
I can't believe I came all the way
to this countryside to see you.

66
00:06:21,459 --> 00:06:23,962
I guess I do love you a lot.

67
00:06:26,064 --> 00:06:27,432
What are you waiting for?
Get your stuff.

68
00:06:31,336 --> 00:06:33,104
I'll let you swim...

69
00:06:33,939 --> 00:06:34,773
again.

70
00:06:56,094 --> 00:06:58,530
(Jeong Gi Tae)

71
00:07:01,499 --> 00:07:02,467
What?

72
00:07:02,467 --> 00:07:03,668
What's going on?

73
00:07:03,668 --> 00:07:05,236
I woke up and you were gone,

74
00:07:05,236 --> 00:07:06,938
and so was that diver girl.

75
00:07:08,607 --> 00:07:09,441
Stop crying.

76
00:07:12,010 --> 00:07:13,311
Did you run away together?

77
00:07:13,845 --> 00:07:15,880
I ran away, but I don't know about her.

78
00:07:17,015 --> 00:07:18,383
Maybe she heard what you said last night.

79
00:07:19,951 --> 00:07:20,785
Me?

80
00:07:21,353 --> 00:07:22,287
What did I say?

81
00:07:24,823 --> 00:07:26,424
I always talk nonsense when I'm drunk.

82
00:07:29,261 --> 00:07:30,262
It's not nonsense.

83
00:07:36,134 --> 00:07:37,869
It's true that I got him killed.

84
00:07:53,184 --> 00:07:55,553
She must've been disappointed in me.

85
00:08:04,362 --> 00:08:06,865
I was disappointed...

86
00:08:08,733 --> 00:08:09,567
in myself.

87
00:08:13,071 --> 00:08:14,406
- Jae Yun.
- Yes?

88
00:08:14,406 --> 00:08:15,273
Hello?

89
00:08:15,273 --> 00:08:17,208
- You really went to get Seo Anna?
- Yeah.

90
00:08:18,043 --> 00:08:19,144
Why would you go and bring her back?

91
00:08:19,144 --> 00:08:21,913
You promised to break up with her
and stay with me.

92
00:08:23,848 --> 00:08:26,851
A rematch between
former youth team rivals.

93
00:08:27,185 --> 00:08:28,520
Doesn't that sound awesome?

94
00:08:29,721 --> 00:08:32,090
And what if I end up losing?

95
00:08:32,090 --> 00:08:33,959
That's impossible.

96
00:08:37,329 --> 00:08:38,997
I know Seo Anna's skills.

97
00:08:38,997 --> 00:08:40,265
Her level is right below yours.

98
00:08:42,934 --> 00:08:45,203
Whatever. I'll leave it up to you, then.

99
00:08:47,772 --> 00:08:49,908
Jeez. She's being so annoying.

100
00:09:01,987 --> 00:09:03,455
We'll start over,

101
00:09:04,122 --> 00:09:04,956
Anna.

102
00:09:09,628 --> 00:09:10,695
I know it's silly.

103
00:09:11,896 --> 00:09:14,065
Even though I knew
what kind of person Jae Yun was,

104
00:09:16,568 --> 00:09:18,603
I came back to Seoul...

105
00:09:19,337 --> 00:09:20,772
just because he said
he'd let me swim again.

106
00:09:40,091 --> 00:09:41,993
It was as if my days in Parang-ri...

107
00:09:42,394 --> 00:09:43,995
didn't mean anything at all.

108
00:10:20,465 --> 00:10:21,967
I think I passed three minutes.

109
00:10:22,534 --> 00:10:23,768
I did pretty well, right?

110
00:10:29,941 --> 00:10:32,110
Holding your breath for a long time
isn't what's important.

111
00:10:34,412 --> 00:10:36,848
Then why am I doing this?

112
00:10:38,049 --> 00:10:40,885
It's to know your limit.

113
00:10:42,420 --> 00:10:44,723
Lasting longer underwater
isn't always a good thing.

114
00:10:46,091 --> 00:10:47,292
You need to know your limit...

115
00:10:49,294 --> 00:10:50,996
so you know when to let go
and make it back up alive.

116
00:10:56,601 --> 00:10:57,669
Yun Deok Hyun...

117
00:10:58,903 --> 00:11:00,405
It was as though his words...

118
00:11:01,873 --> 00:11:02,774
also...

119
00:11:04,643 --> 00:11:05,710
didn't mean anything.

120
00:11:31,436 --> 00:11:32,404
(Seafood Noodles)

121
00:11:38,576 --> 00:11:41,513
These aren't seafood noodles.
They just smell like seafood.

122
00:11:51,723 --> 00:11:53,792
(Best by Sep 16, 2024)

123
00:11:53,792 --> 00:11:54,559
The limit...

124
00:11:56,461 --> 00:11:59,064
Who decides that?

125
00:12:56,888 --> 00:12:58,556
Are we seriously getting this
for Nam Seok U too?

126
00:12:58,556 --> 00:12:59,357
(Seven years ago)

127
00:12:59,357 --> 00:13:01,159
It's not because of him.
It's only because of Jae Hui.

128
00:13:01,159 --> 00:13:02,961
It's as if he's our senior.

129
00:13:05,597 --> 00:13:07,198
Darn it.

130
00:13:08,566 --> 00:13:09,834
Rock, paper, scissors.

131
00:13:12,837 --> 00:13:14,105
Go and prepare it again.

132
00:13:19,144 --> 00:13:20,178
Hurry.

133
00:13:20,178 --> 00:13:21,146
Shut up!

134
00:13:27,852 --> 00:13:29,888
You idiot. I'm holding a gun.

135
00:13:29,888 --> 00:13:30,655
Understand?

136
00:13:31,189 --> 00:13:32,123
Look.

137
00:13:32,557 --> 00:13:33,792
Please, stop.

138
00:13:33,792 --> 00:13:35,527
You must be terrified.

139
00:13:36,595 --> 00:13:37,629
Stop this, sir.

140
00:13:37,862 --> 00:13:39,230
"Stop this, sir."

141
00:13:41,633 --> 00:13:42,968
This is dangerous.

142
00:13:43,602 --> 00:13:45,236
You're right. It's dangerous.

143
00:13:45,704 --> 00:13:48,373
You could get a bullet through your head
if you're not careful.

144
00:13:49,307 --> 00:13:52,043
So just listen to me, you fucker!

145
00:13:56,548 --> 00:13:58,650
I told you to stop bullying Jae Hui.

146
00:13:58,917 --> 00:13:59,684
Didn't I?

147
00:14:01,286 --> 00:14:03,822
Why are you so bent on bullying him?

148
00:14:04,723 --> 00:14:05,557
Why?

149
00:14:07,459 --> 00:14:08,326
"Why?"

150
00:14:08,893 --> 00:14:10,629
There's no reason.

151
00:14:11,263 --> 00:14:12,197
It's just fun.

152
00:14:15,066 --> 00:14:16,334
You bastard.

153
00:14:17,535 --> 00:14:18,403
Die!

154
00:14:19,271 --> 00:14:20,238
Die!

155
00:14:22,674 --> 00:14:23,508
You son of a bitch.

156
00:14:56,574 --> 00:14:58,243
Jae Hui. No.

157
00:14:58,810 --> 00:14:59,644
Jae Hui, no...

158
00:15:00,111 --> 00:15:00,946
Jae Hui.

159
00:15:02,213 --> 00:15:04,049
Jae Hui...

160
00:15:04,049 --> 00:15:04,883
No.

161
00:15:05,283 --> 00:15:07,385
Jae Hui, no...

162
00:15:08,053 --> 00:15:09,788
What are you doing? Get a medic!

163
00:15:11,489 --> 00:15:12,324
Jae Hui...

164
00:15:20,966 --> 00:15:21,800
Gi Tae!

165
00:15:22,701 --> 00:15:23,768
Jeong Gi Tae!

166
00:15:27,505 --> 00:15:28,340
What?

167
00:15:30,442 --> 00:15:31,876
- Jae Hui.
- Jae Hui!

168
00:16:32,971 --> 00:16:33,672
(Baek Su Jeong)

169
00:16:33,672 --> 00:16:34,806
Bitch.

170
00:16:35,440 --> 00:16:38,276
You haven't changed
one bit in the last ten years.

171
00:16:38,944 --> 00:16:39,844
You traitor.

172
00:16:46,251 --> 00:16:47,319
Perhaps...

173
00:16:49,154 --> 00:16:50,622
we might be struggling to survive...

174
00:16:51,189 --> 00:16:52,991
because we don't know our limits.

175
00:17:19,684 --> 00:17:21,886
We don't even know
that we've run out of breath.

176
00:17:32,697 --> 00:17:34,699
You said you were running away,
but you're here.

177
00:17:37,335 --> 00:17:38,270
Hey.

178
00:17:38,270 --> 00:17:39,137
Get up.

179
00:17:40,772 --> 00:17:41,640
Let's eat.

180
00:18:00,525 --> 00:18:01,893
What changed your mind?

181
00:18:02,193 --> 00:18:03,662
You acted like you'd never come.

182
00:18:04,562 --> 00:18:05,931
That's why I came.
So I'll never come back.

183
00:18:07,699 --> 00:18:10,602
Why do you always have to talk like that?

184
00:18:12,637 --> 00:18:14,439
Remember how you asked me
back on the island...

185
00:18:14,439 --> 00:18:16,408
why I was so obsessed with you?

186
00:18:17,075 --> 00:18:17,943
Did I?

187
00:18:20,412 --> 00:18:21,379
Well...

188
00:18:23,448 --> 00:18:25,083
I still can't forget...

189
00:18:27,052 --> 00:18:28,253
the stuff that Jae Hui said.

190
00:18:35,126 --> 00:18:37,429
Slow down. No one's stealing your food.

191
00:18:38,096 --> 00:18:39,664
It's just so tasty.

192
00:18:41,866 --> 00:18:44,469
He really isn't the Special Forces type.

193
00:18:45,236 --> 00:18:46,104
Don't you think?

194
00:18:46,538 --> 00:18:47,572
There's no such thing.

195
00:18:48,106 --> 00:18:50,809
Anyone can adjust after a while.

196
00:18:56,381 --> 00:18:57,382
I...

197
00:18:57,382 --> 00:18:58,617
I actually...

198
00:19:00,518 --> 00:19:02,721
joined the Special Forces
because I wanted to change.

199
00:19:07,559 --> 00:19:09,728
I didn't want to live like this
any longer.

200
00:19:11,696 --> 00:19:12,897
There's nothing wrong with you.

201
00:19:13,698 --> 00:19:15,500
The guys who bullied you are at fault.

202
00:19:16,635 --> 00:19:17,669
Even so...

203
00:19:19,938 --> 00:19:22,007
nothing will change
if I don't do anything.

204
00:19:27,212 --> 00:19:28,179
I should at least...

205
00:19:29,481 --> 00:19:30,649
make an effort.

206
00:19:42,060 --> 00:19:44,362
I wanted to bring you back out
into the world,

207
00:19:47,632 --> 00:19:49,301
but doing nothing
wouldn't change anything.

208
00:19:51,503 --> 00:19:52,470
So...

209
00:19:53,505 --> 00:19:56,041
that's why I've been trying
all sorts of things to convince you.

210
00:20:03,682 --> 00:20:05,016
I'm sorry about this.

211
00:20:05,283 --> 00:20:07,419
I don't have a bank account.

212
00:20:08,286 --> 00:20:09,321
That's a lot.

213
00:20:10,021 --> 00:20:11,423
You're paying for several months
in advance this time?

214
00:20:12,424 --> 00:20:13,825
This is my final payment.

215
00:20:14,659 --> 00:20:15,927
You've been paying for two years,

216
00:20:15,927 --> 00:20:17,896
but it was your first visit, wasn't it?

217
00:20:18,563 --> 00:20:19,931
There are lots of people like you.

218
00:20:20,432 --> 00:20:23,134
It's not easy to see
your loved ones in pain.

219
00:20:25,403 --> 00:20:27,505
Yeah, well... I guess.

220
00:20:29,074 --> 00:20:30,041
How did it go?

221
00:20:34,446 --> 00:20:36,181
He asked why you didn't
come sooner, right?

222
00:20:42,454 --> 00:20:43,555
Come back next time.

223
00:20:44,089 --> 00:20:45,991
We only accept
one month's payment at a time.

224
00:20:54,299 --> 00:20:55,467
I'm sorry.

225
00:20:55,467 --> 00:20:57,035
Please just accept it.

226
00:21:28,199 --> 00:21:29,534
I admire your courage.

227
00:21:30,602 --> 00:21:33,538
I didn't work up the courage.
I'm here to check my limit.

228
00:21:33,939 --> 00:21:35,006
What are you on about?

229
00:21:35,006 --> 00:21:36,007
Come on.

230
00:21:36,675 --> 00:21:37,809
Stop chatting.

231
00:21:38,843 --> 00:21:40,011
Let's start with a warm-up.

232
00:21:40,512 --> 00:21:41,346
Get ready...

233
00:21:55,994 --> 00:21:56,828
Hey.

234
00:21:57,629 --> 00:21:59,731
I heard you brought her back here.

235
00:21:59,731 --> 00:22:00,699
Are you kidding me?

236
00:22:01,066 --> 00:22:01,900
What?

237
00:22:02,834 --> 00:22:04,402
You liked her too, didn't you?

238
00:22:04,903 --> 00:22:05,770
Well...

239
00:22:06,071 --> 00:22:07,706
I like looking at her,

240
00:22:08,273 --> 00:22:10,475
but she has a nasty temper.

241
00:22:10,475 --> 00:22:12,544
Then just watch her quietly.

242
00:22:13,078 --> 00:22:14,346
If she's nice to look at, then it's fine.

243
00:22:15,180 --> 00:22:16,014
Shall I?

244
00:22:20,318 --> 00:22:21,586
She does give me butterflies.

245
00:22:23,054 --> 00:22:23,922
So,

246
00:22:24,356 --> 00:22:26,758
you're going to make her an athlete again?

247
00:22:28,159 --> 00:22:29,094
Of course not.

248
00:22:30,161 --> 00:22:32,564
She can't be an athlete with those skills.

249
00:22:33,365 --> 00:22:34,699
Ye Kyung...

250
00:22:35,100 --> 00:22:36,835
wasn't practicing hard these days,

251
00:22:37,502 --> 00:22:38,670
so I wanted to motivate her and stuff.

252
00:22:40,005 --> 00:22:40,939
"And stuff?"

253
00:22:41,539 --> 00:22:42,374
I wanted...

254
00:22:43,341 --> 00:22:44,943
to sleep with Anna too.

255
00:22:48,113 --> 00:22:50,382
You're insane.

256
00:22:51,216 --> 00:22:52,651
Ye Kyung's sexy...

257
00:22:53,084 --> 00:22:54,452
and Anna's cute.

258
00:22:55,320 --> 00:22:56,788
They're both my style.

259
00:23:02,260 --> 00:23:05,163
To be honest, I already knew...

260
00:23:06,164 --> 00:23:07,565
that this was my limit.

261
00:23:19,878 --> 00:23:20,745
I just...

262
00:23:21,579 --> 00:23:23,114
couldn't let go until now.

263
00:23:57,749 --> 00:23:59,050
It wasn't going to take long.

264
00:24:01,686 --> 00:24:02,754
You'll get yourself killed like that.

265
00:24:03,688 --> 00:24:04,956
You need to let go and come back up.

266
00:24:06,091 --> 00:24:07,092
That's how you survive.

267
00:24:10,495 --> 00:24:11,763
Was Yun Deok Hyun right?

268
00:24:12,931 --> 00:24:15,700
Would I survive if I let go?

269
00:24:20,005 --> 00:24:21,873
Can I really survive...

270
00:24:23,008 --> 00:24:23,975
even if I...

271
00:24:25,343 --> 00:24:26,411
give up swimming?

272
00:24:28,580 --> 00:24:31,082
You're not satisfied
with Han Ye Kyung alone?

273
00:24:32,784 --> 00:24:34,486
Can you really handle both of them?

274
00:24:34,486 --> 00:24:35,420
Hey, Seo Anna!

275
00:24:35,987 --> 00:24:37,355
Why are you stopping? Keep going!

276
00:24:41,059 --> 00:24:42,527
Where is she going?

277
00:24:42,961 --> 00:24:43,762
What?

278
00:24:47,465 --> 00:24:48,266
What?

279
00:24:51,269 --> 00:24:52,170
Are you hurting?

280
00:24:53,305 --> 00:24:54,139
Is it your shoulder?

281
00:24:58,777 --> 00:24:59,611
Are you crazy?

282
00:24:59,611 --> 00:25:00,879
Yeah, I am.

283
00:25:01,846 --> 00:25:03,882
You can't swim if you treat me like this.

284
00:25:04,282 --> 00:25:05,183
I won't, you jerk.

285
00:25:13,024 --> 00:25:13,959
Seo Anna.

286
00:25:15,260 --> 00:25:16,194
Have you lost your mind?

287
00:25:16,628 --> 00:25:17,495
Asshole.

288
00:25:19,798 --> 00:25:21,666
I didn't say anything.

289
00:25:22,801 --> 00:25:23,668
You jerk.

290
00:25:26,638 --> 00:25:29,107
I wasn't planning
on talking it out either.

291
00:25:31,209 --> 00:25:32,177
Han Ye Kyung.

292
00:25:33,511 --> 00:25:35,013
If you keep rolling like that,

293
00:25:36,214 --> 00:25:37,215
you'll end up like me.

294
00:25:39,851 --> 00:25:40,986
Don't trust Coach Cha...

295
00:25:44,823 --> 00:25:45,824
too much.

296
00:25:59,271 --> 00:26:01,373
(Award)

297
00:26:03,241 --> 00:26:04,209
I'm sorry.

298
00:26:04,843 --> 00:26:06,878
I'll find the next tenant myself,

299
00:26:06,878 --> 00:26:08,480
- so just for a month...
- All right.

300
00:26:08,914 --> 00:26:10,548
But you're so young.

301
00:26:10,548 --> 00:26:12,784
Why are you suddenly moving
to the countryside?

302
00:26:17,088 --> 00:26:18,056
I have to...

303
00:26:18,890 --> 00:26:20,625
let things go and go above water...

304
00:26:21,993 --> 00:26:23,161
to survive.

305
00:26:26,865 --> 00:26:29,167
Yes, please do that for me.

306
00:26:30,168 --> 00:26:31,102
Thank you.

307
00:26:47,118 --> 00:26:47,953
Mom.

308
00:26:49,588 --> 00:26:50,922
I'm doing a good job,

309
00:26:52,023 --> 00:26:52,857
right?

310
00:26:53,959 --> 00:26:55,660
There's no need to ask.

311
00:27:02,968 --> 00:27:03,969
Gosh.

312
00:27:04,703 --> 00:27:06,938
When did you ever do what I said...

313
00:27:06,938 --> 00:27:08,440
and stop when I told you to?

314
00:27:09,374 --> 00:27:11,076
You never listened to a word I said.

315
00:27:13,578 --> 00:27:15,046
When did I do that?

316
00:27:17,148 --> 00:27:18,183
I told you,

317
00:27:19,251 --> 00:27:22,821
the color of your medal doesn't matter
the slightest bit.

318
00:27:23,922 --> 00:27:24,789
And it's the same now.

319
00:27:25,624 --> 00:27:28,126
Whether you swim or not doesn't matter.

320
00:27:30,962 --> 00:27:32,764
My daughter, Seo Anna.

321
00:27:33,331 --> 00:27:36,368
Just do what you want, eat healthy,

322
00:27:36,635 --> 00:27:37,636
and live a comfortable life.

323
00:27:38,103 --> 00:27:39,037
That's all I want for you.

324
00:27:44,075 --> 00:27:47,145
I'll always be rooting for you.

325
00:27:50,649 --> 00:27:51,683
Seo Anna,

326
00:27:51,683 --> 00:27:52,617
stay strong!

327
00:28:19,177 --> 00:28:21,012
Do it properly.

328
00:28:21,012 --> 00:28:22,948
Come on, you little brat!

329
00:28:25,784 --> 00:28:26,985
I don't want to do this.

330
00:28:28,820 --> 00:28:31,923
I should've been the one
to go to Seoul, not Anna.

331
00:28:35,226 --> 00:28:36,428
It's not too late, you know.

332
00:28:43,234 --> 00:28:45,370
What? You're back already?

333
00:28:45,670 --> 00:28:47,339
Yeah, I am.

334
00:28:56,514 --> 00:28:57,482
How have you been?

335
00:29:09,294 --> 00:29:10,195
In the end...

336
00:29:11,896 --> 00:29:13,064
I came back to Parang-ri.

337
00:29:16,268 --> 00:29:17,168
But...

338
00:29:17,869 --> 00:29:18,970
things are different from before.

339
00:29:26,678 --> 00:29:28,513
Because the fact that I came back up...

340
00:29:35,320 --> 00:29:37,389
means I'm ready to dive back in.

341
00:29:39,090 --> 00:29:40,025
I'm so hungry.

342
00:29:44,329 --> 00:29:46,765
(Parang-ri diver Jo Mi Hyun)

343
00:30:27,872 --> 00:30:30,308
You're here.

344
00:30:32,310 --> 00:30:33,111
Were you...

345
00:30:34,613 --> 00:30:35,981
waiting for me?

346
00:30:39,718 --> 00:30:42,087
I came to tell you something
before I left.

347
00:30:49,361 --> 00:30:51,263
If it's an explanation about your past,

348
00:30:52,197 --> 00:30:53,064
there's no need.

349
00:30:54,399 --> 00:30:55,600
I didn't look up anything,

350
00:30:57,002 --> 00:30:58,136
and I'm not even curious.

351
00:30:59,571 --> 00:31:00,739
If you're really a bad guy,

352
00:31:02,307 --> 00:31:03,842
the police would've arrested you already.

353
00:31:09,080 --> 00:31:10,115
More than anything,

354
00:31:13,818 --> 00:31:15,120
it's not something...

355
00:31:17,022 --> 00:31:18,490
I should receive an apology for
or forgive.

356
00:31:29,801 --> 00:31:30,635
You should...

357
00:31:33,371 --> 00:31:34,439
swim again.

358
00:31:39,344 --> 00:31:41,212
That's what I came here to tell you.

359
00:31:44,516 --> 00:31:46,651
I was afraid I wouldn't be able to live...

360
00:31:47,652 --> 00:31:48,520
after quitting swimming.

361
00:31:53,458 --> 00:31:55,093
You know you're being silly, don't you?

362
00:31:59,197 --> 00:32:00,865
I felt it while I saw you diving.

363
00:32:00,865 --> 00:32:01,766
You...

364
00:32:02,634 --> 00:32:03,735
can swim again.

365
00:32:04,803 --> 00:32:06,805
Are you giving advice to a professional?

366
00:32:10,408 --> 00:32:11,343
Sorry.

367
00:32:12,377 --> 00:32:13,678
It wasn't my place.

368
00:32:16,181 --> 00:32:18,817
But I'm not scared anymore.

369
00:32:28,360 --> 00:32:29,828
I'm glad you seem okay.

370
00:32:31,129 --> 00:32:31,963
Well, then.

371
00:32:36,001 --> 00:32:36,968
Do you want...

372
00:32:39,804 --> 00:32:40,839
to swim together?

373
00:32:48,713 --> 00:32:49,581
This time,

374
00:32:52,117 --> 00:32:53,251
I'll teach you.

375
00:33:01,760 --> 00:33:03,728
Because now I know that there's someone...

376
00:33:06,831 --> 00:33:08,066
willing to dive into the water...

377
00:33:10,135 --> 00:33:11,202
with me.

378
00:33:35,594 --> 00:33:36,628
What?

379
00:33:36,628 --> 00:33:38,630
How did you know where I live?

380
00:33:39,097 --> 00:33:39,898
Jeez.

381
00:33:39,898 --> 00:33:43,268
I've been chasing Yun Deok Hyun around
for three years.

382
00:33:43,568 --> 00:33:47,072
Tracking down an athlete whose name
and face are known is a piece of cake.

383
00:33:49,307 --> 00:33:50,909
Why are you here, then?

384
00:33:54,546 --> 00:33:56,514
Yun Deok Hyun...

385
00:33:57,115 --> 00:33:59,017
It seems like he went back to the island.

386
00:34:01,319 --> 00:34:03,855
No way. He took his stuff and left.

387
00:34:05,590 --> 00:34:07,125
I'm sure of it.

388
00:34:08,326 --> 00:34:09,261
So...

389
00:34:09,995 --> 00:34:11,196
if you meet him again,

390
00:34:13,398 --> 00:34:14,299
can you...

391
00:34:15,834 --> 00:34:17,168
pull him out of the water?

392
00:34:22,841 --> 00:34:24,542
I saw how he was smiling...

393
00:34:26,711 --> 00:34:28,179
when he was with you.

394
00:34:33,084 --> 00:34:33,952
Hey!

395
00:34:40,792 --> 00:34:41,693
He was smiling...

396
00:34:42,794 --> 00:34:44,396
when he was with me?

397
00:34:51,303 --> 00:34:52,570
Get up.

398
00:35:28,440 --> 00:35:30,442
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
